{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "goqueue-api-collection",
    "name": "GoQueue API",
    "description": "GoQueue - Distributed Message Queue API\n\nA high-performance, distributed message queue combining features from Kafka, SQS, and RabbitMQ.\n\n## Features\n- Topics & Partitions\n- Consumer Groups\n- Message Reliability (ACK/NACK/DLQ)\n- Priority Queues\n- Delayed Messages\n- Schema Registry\n- Transactions\n\n## Quick Start\n1. Set the `baseUrl` variable to your GoQueue server\n2. Create a topic\n3. Publish messages\n4. Consume via consumer groups",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "topicName",
      "value": "orders",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "groupId",
      "value": "order-processors",
      "type": "string"
    },
